isPermaLink="false">http://creditshout.com/?p=13254</guid> <description><![CDATA[<br/>If you fly on American Airlines frequently, you may be able to achieve Elite status in the American Airlines AAdvantage program. With such status comes upgrades and other travel rewards. How can you get Elite status with American Airlines AAdvantage? Let’s explore this and good ways to earn miles in the process. To achieve elite [...]]]></description> <content:encoded><![CDATA[<br/><p><img
src="http://creditshout.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/American-Airlines-260x189.jpg" alt="" title="American-Airlines" width="260" height="189" class="photo" />If you fly on American Airlines frequently, you may be able to achieve Elite status in the American Airlines AAdvantage program. With such status comes upgrades and other travel rewards. How can you get Elite status with American Airlines AAdvantage? Let’s explore this and good ways to earn miles in the process.</p><p>To achieve elite status, you’ll have to earn at least 25,000 miles or fly on 30 flight segments. Miles can be earned by purchasing tickets on American Airlines, American Eagle, American Connection, Alaska Airlines, British Airways, Cathay Pacific, Dragonair, Finnair, Horizon Air, Iberia, Japan Airlines (including J-Air, JAL Express,  JALways,  Japan Asia Airways and Japan Transocean Air), LAN Airlines (including LAN Argentina, LAN Ecuador, LAN Express and LAN Peru), Malev Hungarian Airlines, Mexicana, Quantas, Royal Jordanian, S7 and American Airlines marketed codeshare flights (if the ticket reflects an American Airlines coded flight number).</p><p>Once you’re hit 25,000 miles or 30 flight segments, you’ll achieve AAdvantage Gold Status. At 50,000 miles or 60 segments, you’ll achieve AAdvantage Platinum status. At 100,000 miles or 100 segments, you’ll achieve AAdvantage Executive Platinum status.</p><p><span
id="more-13254"></span><div
class="bigheader">Benefits</div><p>At AAdvantage Gold status, you will have access to complimentary upgrades on full-fare tickets within 24 hours of your flight. You’ll also have access to other upgrades such as companion upgrades. Additionally, you’ll receive the following benefits and more:</p><ul><li>25 percent Elite mileage bonus</li><li>Minimum mileage guarantee</li><li>Special service desk</li><li>Preferred seating</li><li>Priority check-in, security screening and boarding</li><li>Same-day standby</li><li>Waived checked baggage charge</li><li>Discounted Admirals Club membership</li><li>Waived award processing charge</li></ul><p>At AAdvantage Platinum status, you’ll receive the same benefits as with AAdvantage Gold and the following:</p><ul><li>Upgrades on full-fare tickets within 72 hours of your flight</li><li>100 percent Elite mileage bonus</li><li>Oneworld Partner Lounge access</li></ul><p>Once you hit AAdvantage Executive Platinum status, there is a big jump in rewards. In addition to all of the aforementioned awards, you’ll get the following:</p><ul><li>Unlimited complimentary upgrades</li><li>Up to 8 <a
href="http://www.aa.com/i18n/AAdvantage/eliteStatus/upgrades/upgrades.jsp" target="_blank">systemwide upgrades</a> per year (confirmed upgrades at the time of booking as opposed to hoping you’ll get an upgrade a few days before your flight)</li><li>Guaranteed economy class availability</li><li>Waitlist priority for purchased first or business-class tickets</li><li>Waived ticketing service charge</li><li><a
href="http://www.americanairlines.co.uk/i18n/travelInformation/newFlagship_Checkin.jsp?locale=en_GB&amp;anchorLocation=DirectURL&amp;title=ukflagshipcheck-in" target="_blank">Flagship Check-in</a> at London Heathrow Airport (an easier, less hectic way of checking in than the standard procedure)</li><li>Waived award charge</li><li>Expanded availability for reward seats</li></ul><p>As you can see, the benefits rise with each status level and you are more likely to get upgrades with each rise in status, as well.</p><div
class="bigheader">How to Get Upgrades</div><p>If you qualify for upgrades, you may wonder how to go about getting them. In order to get a systemwide upgrade (available for Executive Platinum status members), contact the Elite Service Desk and notify them that you’d like such an upgrade. This can be done at the time of booking or later.</p><p>For standard upgrades, call AAdvantage Reservations at 1-800-882-8880. These can also be requested at the time of booking. However, they will not be confirmed until the period in which they are eligible, such as within 72 hours of your flight for AAdvantage Platinum members.</p><div
class="bigheader">Earning Points with American Airlines</div><p>There are 2 credit cards that are specifically tailored toward American Airlines rewards. They are as follows:</p><p><strong>Citi Gold Select/AAdvantage World MasterCard</strong></p><p><div
